{
  "page": "The Song of the Seven",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/c9/A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg/350px-A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/c9/A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg/525px-A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/c9/A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg/700px-A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:A.M._Sartor_Song_of_the_Seven.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>\"The Song of the Seven\", by A. M. Sartor © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>\"<b>The Song of the Seven</b>\" is a lullaby about the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>. It is made up of seven verses, one for each of the aspects of the god of the Seven, with the exception of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stranger_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Stranger (the Seven)\">Stranger</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Lyrics\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Lyrics</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Lyrics\">Lyrics</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Song_of_the_Seven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Lyrics\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"font-style:italic;padding-left:1em;display:flow-root;\" class=\"poem\">\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Father_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Father (the Seven)\">Father</a>'s face is stern and strong,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">he sits and judges right from wrong.</span><br />\nHe weighs our lives, the short and long,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">and loves the little children.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Mother_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Mother (the Seven)\">Mother</a> gives the gift of life,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">and watches over every wife.</span><br />\nHer gentle smile ends all strife,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">and she loves her little children.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Warrior_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Warrior (the Seven)\">Warrior</a> stands before the foe,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">protecting us where e'er we go.</span><br />\nWith sword and shield and spear and bow,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">he guards the little children.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Crone_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Crone (the Seven)\">Crone</a> is very wise and old,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">and sees our fates as they unfold.</span><br />\nShe lifts her lamp of shining gold<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">to lead the little children.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Smith_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Smith (the Seven)\">Smith</a>, he labors day and night,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">to put the world of men to right.</span><br />\nWith hammer, plow, and fire bright,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">he builds for little children.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Maiden (the Seven)\">Maiden</a> dances through the sky,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">she lives in every lover's sigh.</span><br />\nHer smiles teach the birds to fly,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">and gives dreams to little children.</span><br />\n<br />\nThe Seven Gods who made us all,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">are listening if we should call.</span><br />\nSo close your eyes, you shall not fall,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">they see you, little children.</span><br />\nJust close your eyes, you shall not fall,<br />\n<span class=\"mw-poem-indented\" style=\"display: inline-block; margin-left: 1em;\">they see you, little children.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</p>\n</div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Song_of_the_Seven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Septon\" title=\"Septon\">septon</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_Hill\" title=\"Horn Hill\">Horn Hill</a> sang \"The Song of the Seven\" to <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> and his sisters when they were young to help them sleep. When Samwell and his mother <a href=\"/index.php/Melessa_Florent\" title=\"Melessa Florent\">Melessa</a> sang the song to to the infant <a href=\"/index.php/Dickon_Tarly\" title=\"Dickon Tarly\">Dickon</a>, however, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> reprimanded his wife and heir, as he believed that singing had made Sam weak.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Song_of_the_Seven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Song_of_the_Seven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> sings the song to <a href=\"/index.php/Gilly\" title=\"Gilly\">Gilly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Monster\" title=\"Monster\">her child</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Whitetree\" title=\"Whitetree\">Whitetree</a> to help the babe sleep.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Song_of_the_Seven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Gilly</b>: Did you only sing of six gods? <a href=\"/index.php/Craster\" title=\"Craster\">Craster</a> always told us you <a href=\"/index.php/Southron\" title=\"Southron\">southrons</a> had <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">seven</a>.<br />\n<b>Samwell</b>: Seven, but no one sings of <a href=\"/index.php/Stranger_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Stranger (the Seven)\">the Stranger</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Gilly\" title=\"Gilly\">Gilly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=The_Song_of_the_Seven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_46\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 46\">Chapter 46</a>, Samwell III.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404202117\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.025 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.027 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 569/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 8816/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 1958/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 1615/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 10/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 1/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4993/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   15.655      1 -total\n 63.26%    9.903      4 Template:Ref\n 48.46%    7.587      1 Template:Lyrics\n 42.16%    6.600      4 Template:Ref/core\n 16.72%    2.617      1 Template:Quote\n 1